This case integrates the stiff H2/O2 ignition with EXPLICIT RK4 at the same
deltaT the Rosenbrock23 sibling uses.  It is SUPPOSED to blow up to NaN within a
few steps -- that is the lesson (explicit methods are stability-limited on stiff
chemistry).  runTests skips it (it would trip the NaN guard by design).  Run it
by hand: runCase tutorials/batch/combustion/ignition01_h2o2_rk4
